<p>I responded to the tweet because during my PhD I learned how to create maps in R. I started by recreating a map from the <a href="https://www.usnewsdeserts.com/">University of North Carolinaâ€™s Hussman School of Journalismâ€™s News Deserts</a> project (below). Now, I am working on a personal project mapping the U.S. National and State parks.</p>

<figure>
    
    <a href="/assets/notes-images/nps/nps-2.png" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">
        <img src="/assets/notes-images/nps/nps-2.png" alt="Image: Map of US newspapers by county" class="img-fluid mx-auto d-block" />
    </a>
    
